  "local_port": 34058,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is average cost per couple to travel Bhutan from AHMEDABAD?",
  "response": "Planning a trip to Bhutan from Ahmedabad can be a memorable experience, offering stunning landscapes, rich culture, and unique heritage. The average cost for a couple traveling from Ahmedabad to Bhutan can vary based on factors such as the duration of stay, type of accommodation, mode of transport, and personal preferences. Below is a breakdown to help you estimate the potential costs:\n\n### **1. Flights**\n\n- **Round-Trip Flights (Ahmedabad to Paro):**\n  - **Economy Class:** \u20b920,000 - \u20b935,000 per person\n  - **Total for Couple:** \u20b940,000 - \u20b970,000\n\n  *Note:* Bhutan's main international gateway is Paro Airport. Flights are primarily operated by Druk Air and Bhutan Airlines, often with a stopover in Kolkata or Delhi.\n\n### **2. Visa and Entry Requirements**\n\n- **For Indian Nationals:**\n  - **Visa:** Indian citizens do not require a visa but need to obtain an **Entry Permit** upon arrival.\n  - **Cost:** Approximately \u20b9300 per person.\n\n- **For Foreign Nationals:**\n  - **Visa Fee:** USD 40 per person (approximately \u20b93,200)\n  - **Sustainable Development Fee (SDF):** USD 200 per person per day (approximately \u20b916,000)\n\n  *Since you're traveling from Ahmedabad, if you're an Indian national, the costs are significantly lower.*\n\n### **3. Accommodation**\n\n- **Budget Hotels:** \u20b92,000 - \u20b95,000 per night for a double room\n- **Mid-Range Hotels:** \u20b95,000 - \u20b910,000 per night\n- **Luxury Hotels:** \u20b910,000 and above per night\n\n  *Estimated Total for 5 Nights (Mid-Range):* \u20b925,000 - \u20b950,000\n\n### **4. Transportation Within Bhutan**\n\n- **Private Car Hire:** \u20b93,000 - \u20b95,000 per day\n- **Public Transport/Shared Vehicles:** More economical but less flexible\n- **Domestic Flights (if visiting remote areas):** Additional costs may apply\n\n  *Estimated Total for 5 Days:* \u20b915,000 - \u20b925,000\n\n### **5. Food and Dining**\n\n- **Average Meal Cost:** \u20b9500 - \u20b91,500 per person per day\n- **Total for Couple:** \u20b95,000 - \u20b915,000 for 5 days\n\n### **6. Sightseeing and Activities**\n\n- **Guide Services:** \u20b92,000 - \u20b94,000 per day\n- **Entrance Fees to Monuments/Parks:** \u20b91,000 - \u20b93,000 total\n- **Adventure Activities (Trekking, etc.):** Additional costs may apply\n\n  *Estimated Total:* \u20b910,000 - \u20b920,000\n\n### **7. Miscellaneous Expenses**\n\n- **Shopping, Souvenirs, etc.:** \u20b95,000 - \u20b910,000\n\n### **8. Total Estimated Cost for a Couple**\n\n| **Category**                 | **Estimated Cost (INR)** |\n|------------------------------|--------------------------|\n| Flights                      | \u20b940,000 - \u20b970,000        |\n| Entry Permit (Indian Nationals)| \u20b9600                     |\n| Accommodation                | \u20b925,000 - \u20b950,000        |\n| Transportation               | \u20b915,000 - \u20b925,000        |\n| Food and Dining              | \u20b95,000 - \u20b915,000         |\n| Sightseeing and Activities   | \u20b910,000 - \u20b920,000        |\n| **Total Estimated Cost**     | **\u20b995,600 - \u20b9180,600**    |\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n1. **Book in Advance:** Flights and accommodations often have better rates when booked early.\n2. **Travel Off-Season:** Costs may be lower during the off-peak tourist seasons.\n3. **Customize Your Itinerary:** Depending on your interests, you can adjust accommodations and activities to better fit your budget.\n4. **Consult a Tour Operator:** If you prefer a hassle-free experience, tour packages can be tailored to your budget and preferences.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nFor a comfortable 5-day trip, a couple can expect to spend approximately **\u20b91,00,000 to \u20b91,80,000**. This range can vary based on personal choices, the type of accommodation, and activities planned. Planning ahead and budgeting according to your preferences will help ensure a smooth and enjoyable trip to Bhutan.",
